# Worktree Hygiene

## Core Rule

**Create → work → merge/discard → remove. Same session.**

Never leave a worktree alive after its branch is gone from origin.

## Naming Convention

Always prefix with date:

```
YYYY-MM-DD-<feature>
```

```bash
# Good
git worktree add .claude/worktrees/2026-04-25-bulk-select -b feat/bulk-select

# Bad — no way to tell age at a glance
git worktree add .claude/worktrees/bulk-select -b feat/bulk-select
```

## Setup (EITS-specific)

```bash
cd .claude/worktrees/<name>
ln -s ../../../deps deps       # symlink deps only — NEVER _build
mix compile                    # isolated _build in the worktree
```

**CRITICAL: `rm` is aliased to `rm-trash` — it follows symlinks and trashes the target.**
Always use `unlink` to remove symlinks:

```bash
unlink deps
unlink _build   # if it somehow exists
```

## Cleanup on Merge (Required)

After every PR merge — same session, before moving on:

```bash
# Remove worktree
git worktree remove --force .claude/worktrees/<name>

# Delete remote branch
git push origin --delete <branch-name>

# Prune stale refs
git worktree prune
git fetch --prune
```

## Stale Detection

Find worktrees whose remote branch no longer exists:

```bash
git worktree list --porcelain \
  | grep "^worktree" \
  | awk '{print $2}' \
  | grep "\.claude/worktrees/" \
  | while read wt; do
      branch=$(git -C "$wt" rev-parse --abbrev-ref HEAD 2>/dev/null)
      git ls-remote --heads origin "$branch" | grep -q "$branch" \
        || echo "STALE: $wt  ($branch)"
    done
```

## Bulk Cleanup

Remove everything under `.claude/worktrees/` when doing a full reset:

```bash
# Unlock any locked worktrees first
git worktree list --porcelain \
  | grep -A2 "locked" \
  | grep "^worktree" \
  | awk '{print $2}' \
  | xargs -I{} git worktree unlock {}

# Remove all project worktrees
git worktree list | grep "\.claude/worktrees" | awk '{print $1}' | while read wt; do
  git worktree remove --force "$wt"
done

git worktree prune
```

## Quick Reference

| Situation | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| Creating worktree | Use `YYYY-MM-DD-<feature>` name |
| Setting up deps | `ln -s ../../../deps deps` + `mix compile` |
| Removing symlinks | `unlink deps` (never `rm`) |
| After PR merged | `worktree remove` + `push --delete branch` + `prune` |
| Stale worktrees piling up | Run stale detection, then remove + prune |
| Locked worktree | `git worktree unlock <path>` first |

## Red Flags

- Worktrees named without a date prefix
- Worktree still alive a day after the PR merged
- `_build` symlinked to main project (corrupts main's beam files — `unlink _build` immediately)
- More than ~5 active worktrees at once
